Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.85,0:00:06.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Detective Takagi went somewhere, without telling anyone where he was headed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.48,0:00:15.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The next day, the Detective Boys were waiting outside Police HQ for Detective Takagi, but he wasn't showing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.49,0:00:17.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.44,0:00:21.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you acquainted with Detective Wataru Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.56,0:00:25.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we are, but why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.29,0:00:27.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a stroke of good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.77,0:00:30.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got a gift from him, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.09,0:00:34.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want you to give this to the senior detective he's in love with.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.77,0:00:38.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you mean Detective Sato, who we were just talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.60,0:00:43.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm? You're acquainted with that female detective too?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.36,0:00:43.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.36,0:00:47.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't they getting married soon or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.25,0:00:48.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.20,0:00:50.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're totally in love!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.26,0:00:54.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then here's a message from him for that happy female detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.28,0:00:59.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'That is perishable, so open it quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.82,0:01:03.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you delay, tomorrow and the next day it'll be no good.'{Hokkaidoese misunderstood as normal JP}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.52,0:01:08.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}When we opened the parcel, there was a tablet PC inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.38,0:01:12.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}When it was turned on, the screen showed...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.19,0:01:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.43,0:01:21.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter how many times you try,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.70,0:01:23.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,whether it's in love, cases, today, or tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.71,0:01:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unable to move, Detective Takagi's fatigue leaves him in a desperate state!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.10,0:01:28.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.77,0:01:30.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.86,0:01:33.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.11,0:03:08.37,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Detective Conan is brought to you by these sponsors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.11,0:03:23.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, how is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.50,0:03:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is Takagi alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.82,0:03:27.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.18,0:03:30.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been lying face-down for the last three hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.92,0:03:33.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He just seems to be quite exhausted...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.83,0:03:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police notebook Takagi dropped earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.97,0:03:40.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has anyone reported finding it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.90,0:03:41.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.33,0:03:43.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We haven't heard anything yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.97,0:03:51.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you been able to contact the families from the three suicide cases that Takagi inspected in the Record Office last week?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.05,0:03:51.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.70,0:03:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The family of the first woman, the medical student Yūko Tokugi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, lived in Kōchi,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.20,0:04:00.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but they moved half a year ago, and we haven't been able to locate them yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.67,0:04:08.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The second woman, the English teacher Natalie Kuruma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was born in Hokkaidō, but her only blood relatives were her parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.58,0:04:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and when they were on their way to pick up their daughter's corpse, they got caught up in a traffic accident and both died.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.07,0:04:22.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it seems that the hostess, Kyōka Hiko'ue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, lied about her birthplace when working, so her background is unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.24,0:04:24.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But from what a friend at her workplace said,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.85,0:04:26.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she'd sometimes slip into the Hakata dialect.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.36,0:04:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shikoku, Hokkaidō and Kyūshū...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.61,0:04:33.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're all far enough away to need to stay overnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.34,0:04:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All three suicides happened on the same day, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.38,0:04:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.51,0:04:40.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll be a year the day after tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.20,0:04:43.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.36,0:04:46.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-The picture suddenly started shaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.44,0:04:46.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.85,0:04:49.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This is an earthquake!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.15,0:04:52.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Contact the Japanese Meteorological Agency and find out the epicenter!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.89,0:04:56.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this is live footage, we can narrow down the location!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.37,0:04:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.04,0:05:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-He's shaking quite a lot...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.04,0:05:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't fall, Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.28,0:05:06.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shiratori! Haven't you found out yet?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.56,0:05:08.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.41,0:05:11.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yesterday and today up until now,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.77,0:05:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there have been no earthquakes in any of Japan's 47 prefectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.17,0:05:18.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.22,0:05:19.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.50,0:05:21.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-He's abroad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.68,0:05:31.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like the shaking stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.97,0:05:35.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-There's a crow!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.93,0:05:37.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.64,0:05:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, a crow landed on the pole or whatever the camera is fixed to, and the picture shook from that impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.07,0:05:47.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.63,0:05:55.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, there's an extremely high chance that this is the act of someone connected to the suicide cases who bears a grudge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.87,0:06:01.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Contact the local jurisdictions keeping detailed\Ninvestigation records, and check for the suspect!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.09,0:06:01.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.66,0:06:12.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry about keeping you so late today, kids.\NI bet you're tired from all the questioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.17,0:06:12.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.50,0:06:15.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't you be more worried about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.85,0:06:18.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi'll get sleepy when it gets dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.72,0:06:19.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.83,0:06:21.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if he rolls over in his sleep...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.61,0:06:25.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't worry, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s usually a peaceful sleeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.34,0:06:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sleep together?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.33,0:06:29.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really {\i1}are{\i0} close!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.04,0:06:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhh, it's just that when we're on\Nstakeouts, we take naps in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.95,0:06:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the kidnapper has a grudge against\NDetective Takagi from one of the suicide cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.95,0:06:46.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was actually a murder then since Detective Takagi decided it was suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.19,0:06:47.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.99,0:06:56.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that was the case, he should hold grudges against the other detectives and forensic officers who came to the scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.11,0:07:00.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and it doesn't seem that anyone asked for any of the three cases to be re-investigated.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.15,0:07:01.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.50,0:07:06.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All three cases happened the day after Date{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died in a traffic accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.22,0:07:12.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was in a daze at the scenes, so since I'm an Assistant Inspector, I'm the one who decided they were suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.37,0:07:14.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he has any grudge, it should be against me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.00,0:07:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about if it was that woman going to medical school?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.39,0:07:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she hit that Date detective then commited suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.82,0:07:26.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who hit Date{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was arrested at the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.20,0:07:28.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tokugi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had caused a different accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.67,0:07:31.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about the English teacher?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.21,0:07:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she was dating Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.68,0:07:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.04,0:07:44.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The calendar at Natalie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s place had "date" written all over it in English, but no detective could go on dates every day like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.44,0:07:47.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then isn't it the hostess?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.96,0:07:51.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she killed herself because her boyfriend was caught by that Detective Date?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.96,0:07:54.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that detective was good friends with Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.53,0:08:02.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It {\i1}was{\i0} Date{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who caught Hiko'ue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s boyfriend, but she hung herself in a fit of emotion
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.77,0:08:06.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when the papers the day after Date{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died said that her boyfriend was a marriage fraudster.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.40,0:08:10.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no reason to hold a grudge against the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.78,0:08:17.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, I think it'd be a good idea to find out more about Detective Date from other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.00,0:08:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm? Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.16,0:08:21.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't help but wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.00,0:08:25.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About Detective Date's given name being "Wataru", just like Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.30,0:08:37.58,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's already night...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.35,0:08:40.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's so cold here that I'm freezing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.35,0:08:43.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Maybe I {\i1}am{\i0} gonna die here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.94,0:08:45.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's my fault for getting into this...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.21,0:08:48.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Maybe this is my punishment...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.90,0:08:50.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.95,0:08:53.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.22,0:08:57.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...leaving it in your hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.38,0:09:04.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Date{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.20,0:09:08.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It's up to you now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.75,0:09:13.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No! Come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.13,0:09:14.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've got to get out of this somehow...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.74,0:09:16.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...and tell that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.88,0:09:25.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Tell them the truth for Date{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.22,0:09:33.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It's no use, Superintendent!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.88,0:09:39.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We contacted the network provider, but it seems that an overseas server {\i1}is{\i0} being used.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.49,0:09:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've requested the co-operation of the local investigation authority, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.39,0:09:45.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean that it'll take some time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.14,0:09:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And even if we did find out the source, it could be routed through many more countries...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.11,0:09:55.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An investigation would take much longer, and by the time we find out, Takagi'll have frozen to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.30,0:09:57.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How's Takagi doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.83,0:09:59.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He seems very weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.78,0:10:03.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been moving about all night long.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.07,0:10:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if he's trying to warm himself up, he's just wasting his strength...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.66,0:10:20.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? "It's not a date"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.66,0:10:25.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi really said that before he left, two days ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.02,0:10:26.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.42,0:10:32.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yumi made a joke asking if Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was going on an overnight date at a hot spring, but he just said with a scowl on his face...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.80,0:10:34.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"It's not a date!"...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.44,0:10:41.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But anyway, you said on the phone that you realized something...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.96,0:10:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The way the guy who handed us the tablet talked was a bit odd!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.52,0:10:51.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said "If you delay, tomorrow and the next day it'll be no good."{Hokkaidoese misunderstood as normal JP}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.87,0:10:54.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That {\i1}is{\i0} strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.37,0:10:57.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he said "Tomorrow, or if you delay, the day after tomorrow..." I could understand, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.83,0:11:00.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he's a foreigner proficient in Japanese?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.97,0:11:04.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he really looked Japanese, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.21,0:11:04.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.35,0:11:09.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, among the three suicide cases,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.67,0:11:11.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was there anyone connected to Hokkaidō?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.80,0:11:13.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.97,0:11:16.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The English conversation teacher, Natalie Kuruma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.51,0:11:18.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was born in Hokkaidō.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.83,0:11:24.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then someone connected with her may well be Detective Takagi's kidnapper.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.63,0:11:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.46,0:11:30.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}asatte
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.46,0:11:30.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}ashita-asatte
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.46,0:11:30.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the Hokkaidō dialect, "the day after tomorrow"{asatte} is said as "tomorrow and the next day"{ashita-asatte}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.43,0:11:34.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.11,0:11:37.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was probably Detective Date's girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.46,0:11:39.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Date{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s girlfriend?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.78,0:11:44.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What she had written in English on her calendar almost every day was not "date".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.75,0:11:47.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Date" is spelt "D-A-T-E".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.89,0:11:50.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you read that as romaji, it's the name {\i1}Date{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.75,0:11:54.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was probably a symbol that Detective {\i1}Date{\i0} was staying over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.90,0:11:58.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like Detective Takagi said, "it was not a 'date'!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.03,0:11:59.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.94,0:12:06.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I assumed D-A-T-E meant the English word "date" because she was an English teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.49,0:12:12.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you said she had planned to go out on a date on the day she commited suicide, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.61,0:12:13.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.36,0:12:17.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that meant that he'd promised to take her somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.15,0:12:25.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she waited for him without knowing about Detective Date's traffic accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.25,0:12:29.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and took her own life out of despair, thinking she'd been dumped?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.73,0:12:31.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.70,0:12:39.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi probably finally realized that a year later, and wanted to tell the truth to her family.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.55,0:12:44.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was apparently looking at a photo booth sticker in his notebook and crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.63,0:12:52.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that he'd just confirmed it was Natalie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in that photo booth sticker from the case records last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.90,0:12:54.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wait a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.86,0:12:57.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that about Detective Date?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.60,0:12:59.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's nothing to do with Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.01,0:13:04.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And how about if she told her parents not that her boyfriend's name was Date, which could be confused with the English "date",
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.99,0:13:08.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but that he was Detective Wataru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from Police HQ?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.58,0:13:16.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if Detective Takagi contacted Natalie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s family saying "I want to meet with you to report something about her"...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.41,0:13:22.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They thought that the "Detective Wataru from Police HQ" who'd abandoned her and drove her to suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.00,0:13:27.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,had finally turned up without any worries a year later, and Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} ended up like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.04,0:13:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, when Natalie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s parents were going to pick up her corpse, they had an accident, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.60,0:13:36.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then who picked up her corpse?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.10,0:13:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was an elderly teacher from the same English conversation class.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.55,0:13:43.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also picked up her belongings.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.55,0:13:52.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, the agency involved reported a while ago that that teacher collapsed into tears when they gave him her corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.20,0:13:54.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They came from the same town, and she was like a daughter to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.94,0:13:56.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it's got to true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.11,0:13:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the one who kidnapped Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.98,0:14:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looking at the e-mails on her phone, he convinced himself that it was Detective Takagi who dumped her and made her commit suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.48,0:14:13.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The suspect has been confirmed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.56,0:14:15.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His full name is Ryūsaku Fuemoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.04,0:14:22.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last month, he left the English conversation class due to an illness, and is thought to have returned to his hometown in Hokkaidō.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.10,0:14:25.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His residence in Hokkaidō is unknown,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.88,0:14:30.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but based on the knowledge that he has yet to vacate the flat he previously lived in within the city limits,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.18,0:14:32.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there's a chance that he might still be hiding there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.92,0:14:36.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry there and capture him as soon as you find him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.10,0:14:38.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Make him spit out Takagi's location!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.56,0:14:39.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.49,0:14:57.50,Signs,,0,0,0,,Fuemoto
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.74,0:15:02.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{sign: Fuemoto}Go ahead, the door's open.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.16,0:15:13.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you've finally, {\i1}finally{\i0} managed to find me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.18,0:15:20.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I might end up dozing off and pushing the bomb's trigger while I was waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.14,0:15:23.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So? Is this him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.38,0:15:25.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.64,0:15:26.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.80,0:15:27.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.20,0:15:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, tell me where Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.58,0:15:35.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it you then?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.40,0:15:40.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The senior detective that Wataru Takagi's in love with, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.21,0:15:43.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.00,0:15:47.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like he said, you're quite a beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.10,0:15:51.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even so, he shouldn't have left Natalie—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.64,0:15:57.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now listen up before I end up hitting you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.58,0:16:02.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man you kidnapped was Wataru Takagi, but Natalie's lover was Wataru Date!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.76,0:16:04.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he didn't dump her!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.05,0:16:09.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But she said in an e-mail that\N'Wataru won't come anymore'...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.26,0:16:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course he wouldn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.18,0:16:13.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As that day, he was hit by a car and died!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.95,0:16:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.08,0:16:19.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So hurry up and tell me where Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.88,0:16:27.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me... Don't tell me the wine was poisoned?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.17,0:16:29.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Call an ambulance! Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.48,0:16:30.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.13,0:16:32.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.05,0:16:33.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-He's...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.55,0:16:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where? Where is he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.43,0:16:36.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.08,0:16:44.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.90,0:16:50.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Sato! What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.09,0:16:54.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on? Did you capture the suspect?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.25,0:16:56.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened? Say something, Sato!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.60,0:16:57.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.53,0:16:59.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Superintendent, unfortunately...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.55,0:17:04.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The death of the suspect, Ryūsaku Fuemoto was just confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.76,0:17:11.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that the wine he was drinking at the time we entered had poison in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.77,0:17:13.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The suspect's dead?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.59,0:17:15.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was he poisoned by someone?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.22,0:17:20.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the bottle of poison had been placed next to his wine bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.31,0:17:24.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that he decided to end his own life when the police arrived to start with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.78,0:17:31.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing that he possessed a bomb, he likely\Nintended to blow himself up if forcibly secured.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.25,0:17:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if he had time{freedom?} to talk, then he'd\Ndrink the poison and watch us despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.83,0:17:40.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As it seems that the suspect held a grudge against the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.60,0:17:43.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you tell him it was a misunderstanding?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.45,0:17:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I told him that he kidnapped Wataru Takagi because he mistook him for Wataru Date, also from Police HQ,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.85,0:17:57.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and that the motive for Natalie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s suicide was not that he dumped him, but because he died in a traffic accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.68,0:18:05.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But by the time I could tell him, he'd already drunk the poison, and before he could tell me Sergeant Takagi's location, he...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.85,0:18:09.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have any clues been found at the suspect's residence?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.81,0:18:10.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.56,0:18:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're searching now, but not yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.22,0:18:19.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing we found was Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s mobile, which was probably taken from him when he was kidnapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.89,0:18:23.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the inbox are several e-mails from the suspect,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.48,0:18:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and among them, there's one saying that while the suspect did intend to come and meet Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} directly,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.43,0:18:37.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he felt unwell, so he would send Takagi an airline ticket he bought for himself, and asked Takagi to use it to visit him...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.21,0:18:42.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's also an unsent e-mail addressed to me, which we believe was written by the culprit,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.56,0:18:46.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,saying "A present from Detective Takagi was left in the shrubbery in front of the Police HQ".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.93,0:18:53.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he probably originally intended to hand over the tablet by doing so.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.60,0:18:59.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then he happened to meet children who knew Takagi, and entrusted the tablet to them...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.09,0:19:04.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. That way, there's no chance of it being taken by someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.20,0:19:09.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are there any other e-mails that hint at where Takagi is?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.08,0:19:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.00,0:19:12.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just "I'll meet you when you get to the airport".
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.59,0:19:15.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I'll leave you in charge of continuing to search the flat!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.79,0:19:16.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.44,0:19:20.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's unlikely they'll find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.59,0:19:21.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.57,0:19:28.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, we're up against someone who only gave us a tablet on which we can see video of Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.67,0:19:33.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most of the functions have been disabled, all the markings on the back have been scraped off,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.50,0:19:38.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the video is sent through an overseas server, so we can't tell its source.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.77,0:19:42.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he planned to commit suicide in front of the police to begin with,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.53,0:19:46.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then I don't think he would've left behind\Nanything which could pinpoint the location.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.93,0:19:51.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Normally, we'd assume it to be the\Nsuspect's birthplace, Hokkaidō, but...{check TL}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.10,0:19:55.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just in case, we're checking with local construction contractors, but...{check TL}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.28,0:20:02.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There haven't been any reports of Takagi being spotted at a four-story building site as shown in the video yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.85,0:20:07.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only clue left is the video of Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.56,0:20:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it started raining or snowing, we could\Nnarrow down the location, but it hasn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.88,0:20:15.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing that showed up was a crow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.44,0:20:16.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A crow showed up?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.33,0:20:18.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.51,0:20:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you recorded it, then let us see it too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.34,0:20:25.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Children know all sorts of things about animals that adults don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.78,0:20:26.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.01,0:20:33.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just an ordinary crow...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.50,0:20:34.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.69,0:20:37.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But look, its neck is gray, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.59,0:20:40.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}T-That's a Western Jackdaw!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.67,0:20:42.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But I thought they were...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.81,0:20:45.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato, reporting in!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.10,0:20:46.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So? Did you learn anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.40,0:20:48.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.80,0:20:55.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the data on his computer had been deleted, and we're trying to find out how he obtained the bomb, but nothing yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.65,0:20:56.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.37,0:20:59.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So? How's Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.26,0:21:01.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. He's still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.65,0:21:03.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although he seems quite weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.79,0:21:06.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.94,0:21:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.17,0:21:10.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s been moving around since yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.85,0:21:13.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought he was moving because he was cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.50,0:21:16.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but he was actually using the edge of the plank to try and cut the rope on his legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.60,0:21:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And just now, he cut them!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.66,0:21:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! If he puts his legs on either side of the plank,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.23,0:21:24.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's less likely he'll fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.78,0:21:25.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.23,0:21:29.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.23,0:21:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's doing something with his legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.20,0:21:34.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't he trying to pull the sheet on the plank closer?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.29,0:21:37.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he covers himself with it, he could stop his body temperature dropping a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.21,0:21:44.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be! He dropped it!
